BFN 

  [Text] Baykan, May 24 (A.A) -- Terrorists who raided 
Ardicli village of Baykan District in southeastern Siirt 
Province, killed seven people including three children, and 
wounded another five, it was reported on Tuesday. 
  They escaped after the attack when security forces arrived 
on 
the scene of the raid. 
  Officials said that operations were started to catch the 
terrorists. 

